Mach numbers smaller than six are found\nto best explain the observational data. Generally, only a probability of 70%\nwas found that our models explain the current observations. This is caused by\nnot well understood selection effects in the observational sample and the\nsimplified assumptions in the models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Feb 2006 16:42:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
