{"id":"quant-ph/0602037","submitter":"Paolo Perinotti Dr.","authors":"Giacomo M. D'Ariano, Paolo Perinotti, Massimiliano F. Sacchi","title":"Superbroadcasting of conjugate quantum variables","comments":"7 pages, 1 eps figures. Accepted for publication on Europhysics\n  Letters","journal-ref":"Europhys. Lett. 75, 195 (2006)","doi":"10.1209/epl/i2006-10105-x","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  We consider the problem of broadcasting arbitrary states of radiation modes\nfrom N to M>N copies by a map that preserves the average value of the field and\noptimally reduces the total noise in conjugate variables. For N>=2 the\nbroadcasting can be achieved perfectly, and for sufficiently noisy input states\none can even purify the state while broadcasting--the so-called\nsuperbroadcasting. For purification (i.e. M<=N), the reduction of noise is\nindependent of M. Similar results are proved for broadcasting with\nphase-conjugation. All the optimal maps can be implemented by linear optics and\nlinear amplification.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Feb 2006 10:26:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 19 May 2006 07:59:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
